text: Sara Serrat Reyes (born 15 September 1995) is a Spanish footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Primera División club Sevilla FC and the Spain women's national team. ==Club career== Sara left her longtime club Sporting de Huelva in 2019. ==International career== Sara was included in the Spain's provisional squad for the 2015 FIFA Women's World Cup.Spain's provisional squad for the Women's World Cup She played her first match in 2019. ==Honours== *Copa de la Reina de Fútbol (1): 2015, ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football goalkeepers Category:Spanish women's footballers Category:Andalusian footballers Category:People from Huelva Category:Spain women's international footballers Category:Primera División (women) players Category:Sporting de Huelva players Category:Sevilla FC (women) players
